<p>The dogs woke me up around 4am, and I went outside.  The moon, close to full,
shown through clear skies.  Setting a light the bitter cold snow, which twinkled
as though themselves stars on a white sky.</p>
<div class="verse">
<p>Deep indigo shroud<br />
Pierced and gouged<br />
Light reflected spills<br />
Upon white fields<br />
Twinkling a promise<br />
Of the morrow rise<br /></p>
</div>

<aside  role="note" class="margin">

<p><small>Often my first entries will be related to what I‚Äôve read.  However, the above
poem needed to be written.  Capturing at least a bit of that memory.</small></p>
</aside>

<p>I read <a href="https://soatok.blog/2025/01/14/dont-use-session-signal-fork/">Don‚Äôt Use Session (Signal Fork)</a>; and this stinks of someone creating a
platform that eases well-funded actors attempting to crack encryption.</p>
<p>In reading <a href="https://shkspr.mobi/blog/2025/01/book-review-rules-for-radicals-a-pragmatic-primer-for-realistic-radicals-by-saul-alinsky/">Book Review: Rules for Radicals- A Pragmatic Primer for Realistic
Radicals by Saul Alinsky</a>, I added <cite data-id="bcb64ed8-9582-41d6-a224-21152330a2f9">Rules for Radicals</cite> by Saul D. Alinksy to my shopping list.  The salient point,
of the review, is the book helps equip change agents by asking ‚ÄúWhat is your
theory of change?‚Äù</p>
<p>Reading <a href="https://nesslabs.com/collective-curiosity?utm_source=rss&amp;utm_medium=rss&amp;utm_campaign=collective-curiosity">The Multiplier Effect of Collective Curiosity</a> leads with an ancient
practice of walking and wondering together.  I‚Äôve done this in past meetings and
can say it was some of the most transformative conversations I‚Äôve had.  Rarely
is there ‚Äúlone genius‚Äù instead this is an effort of collaboration and
conversation.  Each building upon what we share.</p>
<p>In <a href="https://lithub.com/lit-hub-daily-january-15-2025/">Lit Hub Daily: January 15, 2025</a> I learned about <a href="https://www.thenation.com/article/archive/olga-tokarczuk-empusium-realism/">Olga Tokarczuk‚Äôs New Rules
for Realism | The Nation</a> which reviews <cite data-id="c51d973a-21c0-406e-86cd-c334769cfc59">The Empusium</cite> by Olga Tokarczuk; which I added to my shopping list.  Why?  Olga‚Äôs
anti-national (e.g. how do we move away from tribalism); and to move forward
we‚Äôre going to look at how to reduce our us vs. them mindsets.</p>
<p>Read <a href="https://baty.net/journal/2025/01/15/why-am-i-not-taking-pictures">Why am I not taking pictures?</a>, I responded/reflected and wrote 
<cite><a href="https://takeonrules.com/2025/01/15/re-why-am-i-not-playing-games/">Re: Why am I not playing games?</a></cite>.  This makes two responses to Jack in as many days.</p>

