<aside  role="note" class="margin">

<p><small>I had heard of SyncThing but didn‚Äôt use it.  In part because how it was
originally used was conflated with a gaslighting mansplaining experience.  But
don‚Äôt throw the technology used out with the people using it.  Now the people
developing it?</small></p>
</aside>

<p>I started experimenting with syncthing; easy enough to use.  Can replace my
Cloud Drive (if I get one more device in the loop).  However, I must consider
how to make this available for my family.  I‚Äôm using <a href="https://github.com/catfriend1/syncthing-android">Syncthing-Fork</a> on my
Android (as found on <a href="https://docs.syncthing.net/users/contrib.html">Community Contributions ‚Äî Syncthing documentation</a>) and <code>brew install syncthing</code> on my Mac.  It‚Äôs just a bit much for non-programmers; but I
think there‚Äôs some documentation to help.</p>

