<p>I chuckled as I learned about <a href="https://zadzmo.org/code/nepenthes/">ZADZMO code</a>, namely Nepenthes:</p>

<blockquote  class="h-cite">

<p>This is a tarpit intended to catch web crawlers. Specifically, it&rsquo;s targeting
crawlers that scrape data for <span>Large Language Models</span> (<abbr title="Large Language Models">LLMs</abbr> <small><a class="ref" rel="tag opener" aria-label="Other site-wide references of ‚ÄúLarge Language Models‚Äù" title="Other site-wide references of ‚ÄúLarge Language Models‚Äù" href="https://takeonrules.com/site-map/glossary/#abbr-dfn-LLM">üìñ</a></small>)</p>
<ul>
<li>but really, like the plants it is named
after, it&rsquo;ll eat just about anything that finds it&rsquo;s way inside.</li>
</ul>

</blockquote>

<p>I‚Äôm eager for <abbr title="Large Language Model">LLM</abbr>
